differentiation and only costs $300.

00:01:08.860 --> 00:01:14.640
Pembient is hoping to prevent the extinction
of rhinos by 3D-bioprinting their horns.

00:01:14.640 --> 00:01:20.820
The western black rhino went extinct in 2011
due to poaching for its valuable keratin.

00:01:20.820 --> 00:01:26.660
The horns that Pembient are printing are indistinguishable
from the real thing even down to the molecular

00:01:26.660 --> 00:01:31.250
level, and they hope to significantly lower
the value of Rhino horns by introducing the

00:01:31.250 --> 00:01:33.700
product to the market later this year.

00:01:33.700 --> 00:01:38.110
Researchers from Columbia University have
created the world’s thinnest lightbulb.

00:01:38.110 --> 00:01:44.430
By using a graphene coating that can withstand
temperatures as high as 2500 degrees celsius

00:01:44.430 --> 00:01:49.210
they’re able to build a filament that’s
atomically thin but able to generate visible

00:01:49.210 --> 00:01:50.210
light.

00:01:50.210 --> 00:01:54.210
And they hope to build circuits that use photons
instead of electrons to pave the way for large-scale,

00:01:54.210 --> 00:01:58.310
flexible, atomically thin, transparent light
emitters.

00:01:58.310 --> 00:02:03.020
Another team at Columbia University built
a miniature car powered by the air’s natural

00:02:03.020 --> 00:02:04.070
humidity.

00:02:04.070 --> 00:02:08.830
Using microscopic moisture-sucking spores
they were able to build a turbine engine that

00:02:08.830 --> 00:02:11.290
rotates as water evaporates.

00:02:11.290 --> 00:02:16.319
Evaporation is a stronger force than wind
or waves and has previously been untapped

00:02:16.319 --> 00:02:18.219
from an energy perspective.

00:02:18.219 --> 00:02:22.269
The team believes this breakthrough could
someday lead to generating energy via natural

00:02:22.269 --> 00:02:23.599
evaporation.

